abstract: Emmy Awards, which were broadcast on Fox at same time as NBC's Sunday Night Football, draws in only 11.9 million viewers, lowest ratings in history of show.
lead_paragraph: Just 11.9 million viewers tuned in to Fox Sunday night as the Emmy Awards went up against the Green Bay Packers and Seattle Seahawks on NBC.

headline.main: Emmy Awards Audience Drops to New Low
headline.print_headline: N.F.L. Game Helps Push Emmy Ratings to a New Low
